# Flask Guidance

## Project Context

- Flask version: {{ flask_version | default("detected by Akira") }}
- App pattern: {{ app_pattern | default("application factory or module app") }}
- Blueprint style: {{ blueprint_style | default("feature-oriented blueprints") }}

## Application Structure

- Prefer an application factory when the project already uses one.
- Register blueprints in one predictable place.
- Keep configuration loading separate from request handling.
- Initialize extensions once, then bind them to the app during startup.
- Keep view functions thin and delegate business logic to services.

## Request Handling

- Validate request data at the boundary before calling domain code.
- Return explicit status codes for create, update, delete, and error paths.
- Use `url_for()` for internal URL generation.
- Keep `g`, `request`, and `current_app` usage near framework boundaries.
- Keep JSON response shapes consistent across success and error cases.
- Use decorators sparingly and keep authorization behavior easy to trace.

