## Testing Hooks

- Use the app factory to create isolated test apps.
- Prefer fixtures for app, client, and database setup.
- Assert response status, headers, and JSON bodies.
- Keep extension state isolated between tests.

## Configuration

- Prefer app config keys over scattered direct environment reads.

## Avoid

- Import-time app creation when the project uses factories.
- Business rules hidden inside view functions.
- Direct environment reads scattered throughout views.
- Swallowing exceptions without logging or returning a clear response.
